message: Undid revision 762840694 by [[Special:Contributions/Chrisieboy|Chrisieboy]] ([[User talk:Chrisieboy|talk]])  the article is not only about UK....  So don't put UK again and again....  Don't engage in edit war...

BSC optometry, or Bachelor of optometry is taught all over the world, not only in UK...  So UK is omitted from the Infobox to stop confusion.   And, BSC optometry is an honours course, but bachelor of optometry is not....  So hons is omitted.

The whole world except US and Canada follows the bsc optometry or B.optom....  So its not required to mention UK...  As readers will only think that only UK, US and Canada teach optometry by seeing the Infobox.
Add description about UK optometry in UK section.

This is a English Wikipedia page. This represents the whole world. Mr.  Chrisieboy don't  change this Infobox again by omitting Commonwealth countries and putting only UK.. And mind it that BSC is a honours course, BOptom is not. Broaden ur knowledge.
Sentence "opthalmic optician in UK"  removed....  CITATIONS provided  describe name prior to year 2000... At present optometrist are called optometrist in the UK, not opthalmic optician!
